                'encode_title' => 'record-floods-devastate-eastern-australia',
                'seo_title' => NULL,
                'stitle' => NULL,
                'title' => 'Record floods devastate eastern Australia',
            'news' => '<h2 data-end="371" data-start="282" style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size:16px;"><strong data-end="398" data-start="373">Sydney, July 20, 2025</strong> &mdash; A catastrophic wave of flooding tore through <strong data-end="467" data-start="446">eastern Australia</strong> on Friday, leaving behind a trail of devastation across <strong data-end="558" data-start="524">northern New South Wales (NSW)</strong>. Entire towns have been swallowed by rising waters, more than <strong data-end="672" data-start="621">50,000 people have been cut off from assistance</strong>, and at least <strong data-end="716" data-start="687">four lives have been lost</strong> in what authorities are calling <strong data-end="810" data-start="749">one of the most destructive flood events in recent memory</strong>.&nbsp;The floodwaters, driven by days of relentless rainfall and overburdened river systems, have <strong data-end="958" data-start="905">inundated homes, roads, farms, and infrastructure</strong>, while emergency services remain overwhelmed. The worst-hit regions, located <strong data-end="1076" data-start="1036">approximately 400 km north of Sydney</strong>, are now grappling with <strong data-end="1162" data-start="1101">power outages, water shortages, and blocked access routes</strong>, with helicopters being used to airdrop essentials into isolated communities.</span></span></h2>

<h3 data-end="1283" data-start="1247" style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</h3>

<h2 data-end="1898" data-start="1850" style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size:22px;">&nbsp;<strong data-end="1898" data-start="1857">Extent of Damage &mdash; Flood Impact Chart</strong></span></span></h2>

