                'encode_title' => 'businesses-rely-more-on-social-media-than-traditional-advertising-in-2025',
                'seo_title' => NULL,
                'stitle' => NULL,
                'title' => 'Businesses Rely More on Social Media Than Traditional Advertising in 2025',
                'news' => '<p data-end="513" data-start="281">In a major shift in marketing strategy, small and medium businesses are now spending more on <strong data-end="402" data-start="374">social media advertising</strong> than on traditional print, radio, or even TV ads, according to a new global report by <strong data-end="512" data-start="489">StatMarket Insights</strong>.</p>

<p data-end="692" data-start="515">The report shows that over <strong data-end="570" data-start="542">68% of marketing budgets</strong> for startups and e-commerce businesses are now dedicated to platforms like <strong data-end="691" data-start="646">Facebook, Instagram, TikTok, and LinkedIn</strong>.</p>

<p data-end="935" data-start="694">&ldquo;This is where the customers are,&rdquo; said <strong data-end="748" data-start="734">Ruhul Amin</strong>, CEO of Dhaka-based clothing brand UrbanThreads. &ldquo;We used to do billboards and newspaper ads, but a viral TikTok video now gives us more sales than a month&rsquo;s worth of offline promotion.&rdquo;</p>

<p data-end="1252" data-start="937">Major platforms have introduced advanced AI targeting tools, allowing small businesses to reach hyper-specific audiences, track conversions in real-time, and adjust their campaigns instantly. However, the rising cost of paid ads and competition for visibility are challenges for smaller brands with limited budgets.</p>',
