            245 => 
            array (
                'id' => 301,
                'uuid' => '628854c2-6a0f-4a02-b5c3-656d71767858',
                'news_id' => 301,
                'language_id' => 1,
                'category_id' => 88,
                'sub_category_id' => NULL,
                'encode_title' => 'social-media-misinformation-sparks-concern-ahead-of-national-elections',
                'seo_title' => NULL,
                'stitle' => NULL,
                'title' => 'Social Media Misinformation Sparks Concern Ahead of National Elections',
                'news' => '<p data-end="1585" data-start="1380">As countries across the world prepare for key elections in late 2025, governments and watchdog groups are raising alarm over the spread of <strong data-end="1558" data-start="1519">misinformation and deepfake content</strong> on social media platforms.</p>

<p data-end="1882" data-start="1587">In a recent incident in the Philippines, a viral AI-generated video falsely showing a presidential candidate making controversial statements was viewed over 2 million times before being flagged and removed. Similar incidents have been reported in Bangladesh, Brazil, and parts of Eastern Europe.</p>

<p data-end="2070" data-start="1884">Experts warn that <strong data-end="1939" data-start="1902">AI-generated political propaganda</strong>, shared rapidly on platforms like <strong data-end="1998" data-start="1974">X (formerly Twitter)</strong> and <strong data-end="2015" data-start="2003">Facebook</strong>, can erode public trust and influence voting behavior.</p>

<p data-end="2320" data-start="2072">&quot;Platforms must act faster. Content moderation alone isn&#39;t enough,&quot; said <strong data-end="2165" data-start="2145">Dr. Sadia Khatun</strong>, a political science professor at Dhaka University. &ldquo;We need stronger laws, transparent algorithms, and better public education to deal with this crisis.&rdquo;</p>

<p data-end="2478" data-start="2322">Tech giants including Meta and YouTube claim to be enhancing their detection systems and increasing fact-checking partnerships ahead of the election season.</p>',
                'image' => 'RmNdXr9bIYDHKW2NPyfsEqWRSKBaEoZrq1nWhF5F.webp',
