                'stitle' => NULL,
                'title' => 'WWE Evolution Returns: All‑Women Main Event Broadcast on Netflix & Peacock',
                'news' => '<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;">Seven years after its debut, WWE Evolution returned with gusto&mdash;and a renewed mission&mdash;by staging an all-women&rsquo;s flagship event on Netflix and Peacock at State Farm Arena, attended by 8,351 fans. The electrifying main event saw Naomi cashing in her Money in the Bank contract mid-match to defeat Iyo Sky and Rhea Ripley, capturing Raw&rsquo;s Women&rsquo;s World Championship in a stunning triple-threat finish.&nbsp;Wikipedia Earlier on the card, Naomi lost a brutal No Holds Barred match to Jade Cargill, officiated by special referee Bianca Belair, underlining the night&rsquo;s intensity.</span></span></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;">Supporting matches featured Tiffany Stratton retaining SmackDown&rsquo;s Women&rsquo;s Championship by defeating Trish Stratus, while Becky Lynch held Raw&rsquo;s Women&rsquo;s Intercontinental title in a triple-threat victory over Lyra Valkyria and Bayley. Later, Stephanie Vaquer won the Evolution Battle Royal to earn a title match at SummerSlam in Paris. Wikipedia This second Evolution event marks more than a sequel</span></span></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;">it signals WWE&#39;s recommitment to women&rsquo;s wrestling as a premier attraction, elevating full-length women-only PPVs into mainstream platforms and global streaming services.&nbsp;<br />
Wikipedia Critics and fans alike praised WWE&rsquo;s strategic shift: Evolution&rsquo;s placement on Netflix and Peacock made it accessible globally, while the inclusion of talent across Raw, SmackDown, and NXT demonstrated a unified female roster elevation. Industry analysts see this event as a potential turning point for gender representation in wrestling entertainment.&nbsp;</span></span><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:Verdana,Geneva,sans-serif;">Amid the broader week of sports stories, WWE Evolution stands out as a cultural moment&mdash;spanning athleticism, storytelling, and inclusivity. As SummerSlam approaches, the ripple effects from Evolution&rsquo;s success are expected to shape future female-centric main events.</span></span></p>',
